	From: Chris Lindblad &lt;CJL%MIT-OZ@MIT-MC.ARPA&gt;

	MKL@SRI-NIC won't do it, because he says
	that then NIC would have to know about the AI.MIT.EDU domain.
	Instead, he wants to set the servers to the 52.128.IN-ADDR.ARPA
	domain to be the same as those for the MIT.EDU domain, and then
	those servers should delegate further to the servers I wanted.

Yeah, MKL is right, and he gives the appropriate response:

	    I think you should send your in-addr requests off to the
	    MIT.EDU domain maintainer then...

A domain like AI.MIT.EDU is created for the explicit purpose of removing
the responsibility for that section of the namespace from the NIC.
Can you say "de-centralizing" ? I knew you could.

/jordan

